{{notability|date=July 2018}} {{Italic title}} '''''Cybaris''''' is a biannual [[law review]] published by [[Mitchell Hamline School of Law]]. It was established in 2010 and focuses on [[intellectual property law]]. ''Cybaris'' was featured in an article published by ''[[Patently-O]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.patentlyo.com/patent/2010/05/bits-and-bytes-cybaris.html |title=Bits and Bytes: Cybaris - Patent Law Blog |publisher=Patently-O |date=2010-05-17 |accessdate=2012-08-28}}</ref> The founding [[editors-in-chief]] were Jennell Bilek and Ryan C. Smith (2010). The current editor-in-chief is Molly R. Littman.
''Cybaris'' has its own searchable database in [[Westlaw]] (CYBARIS),{{clarify|date=August 2012}} and is included [[Westlaw]]'s index of law reviews (TP-ALL).
